So I tried to do everything right. I bought powdered almonds because my Mom's food processor can hold about one onion chopped and I would have been there all night grinding almonds. Then, when I discovered that my Mom had lent the kitchen scale to my sister, I used math to figure out the right amount of almonds to put in the recipe. I sifted them to make sure that there were no lumps. Then I sifted the icing sugar and combined the two of them. So far so good. I even went as far as to clean the bowl and the beaters with some white vinegar (old chef's trick) before putting the carefully separated egg whites in it. I added only a pinch of salt and 1/4 tsp of cream of tartar. Next, I beat them to the soft peak stage. So far so good. Maybe I'm just too tired from all these holiday preparations - I don't know - but I added the icing sugar and almond mixture to the egg whites next..... @#$%^&*! Of course, there was no stiff peaks to be had. They completly deflated. To make matters worse, I added the raspberries - carefully strained raspberries - and it turned into pink soup. So I went so far as to try to pour them onto the cookie sheet and bake them at 275 for 20 minutes. They were gimpy-looking pink twoonies instead of fluffy pink pillows. Maybe I'll dip them in the ganache, but I'm not serving these things on Christmas as planned. I guess we're not having Christmas cookies this year.... (My Mom's weight watchers cookies don't count) Well, I think that this recipe is going into the dumpster. You can't succeed at everything...

