Rating: 4
I realize that there are some things that need to be tweaked in this recipe, but they are simple, and if you do them, it really is actually a great recipe. Put a couple pinches of salt in, not 3/4 tsp. Pipe out the batter twice as big as it says to. Bake for a bout 7-8 minutes on each rack. I made these small adjustments and they turned out perfect, i made three batches! Also, its not essential, but I found a few other things helpful, especially if you are into presentation: If you tap the cookie sheets after you pipe out the batter, it helps get rid of any bubbles in the meringue. I let them sit for an hour before putting them in the oven, it mades the tops perfect! If you want to get really nit-picky, I would get a frosting bag liner to use for piping, rather than a ziplock, or else they come out a little oval shaped. If you pipe the ganache onto the rounds, rather than spread, you get this beautiful uniform filling that gives them that "store-bought" look!

