Rating: 3
My macarons did not turn out well the first time. But, after reading some blog entries, the second batch turned out really well! Some tips: The almond measurements are a little confusing. If you're using sliced blanched almonds, use 6 oz. If you're using whole blanched almonds, use 2 cups. I'd advise using the sliced almonds. After grinding the almonds, sift the powder with the sugar. This helps keep them from clumping. Don't over-mix the meringues and almond mixture. If you're putting the mix into a baggie or pastry bag, they will mix and deflate even more during that step (and using the bag makes them easier to shape).

