Dear afrodite131: I would recommend using parchment paper rather than wax paper. Parchment paper is slippery (not waxy), so cookies don't stick. A Silpat mat also works well. If you cannot find parchment paper locally, try an online website - it shouldn't be very expensive. It's a fabulous addition to your basic kitchen "utensils" if you like to bake! Try the recipe again, this time with parchment paper, and I think you'll have better success. Good luck!

